Package: UniFORM
Type: Package
Title: Universal ImmunoFluorescence nORMalization for Multiplex Tissue Imaging
Version: 1.0.0
Authors@R: c(
    person("Mark Kunlun", "Wang", 
           email = "wangmar@ohsu.edu", 
           role = c("aut"),
           comment = "Original Python implementation"),
    person("Asim", "Waqas", 
           email = "asim.waqas@moffitt.org", 
           role = c("aut", "cre"),
           comment = "R implementation")
    )
Description: UniFORM_R provides robust normalization methods for multiplex 
    immunofluorescence data. It uses histogram-based cross-correlation and 
    Gaussian Mixture Model analysis to harmonize intensity measurements across 
    different samples, batches, and experimental conditions. This R 
    implementation maintains full compatibility with the original Python 
    UniFORM pipeline while following R package conventions.
